<paragraph pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
<taxonomicName LSID="FBDDCC5A-F779-5F2C-AF42-B92CEA5BE4F3" authority="Hassk. (= C. polot Merr.)" authorityName="Hassk. (= C. polot Merr.)" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Claoxylon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Claoxylon indicum" order="Malpighiales" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="indicum">Claoxylon indicum Hassk. (= C. polot Merr.)</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="name">
<paragraph pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Name.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">English</emphasis>
: claoxylon.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="range">
<paragraph pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Range.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="65" pageNumber="66">China, India, Indonesia, Malaysia, New Guinea, Thailand, and Vietnam. In Myanmar, found in Bago, Kayin, Mon, Rakhine, and Taninthayi.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="uses">
<paragraph pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Uses.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Bark</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Leaf</emphasis>
: Finely ground and smeared on the chest to treat tightness. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Leaf</emphasis>
: Used as a purgative.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
In China a decoction of the leaf is taken internally for various ailments. From Hainan and Myanmar to Sumatra the leaves are used as a purgative, and the finely ground bark mixed with macerated leaves is rubbed onto the chest for congestion (
<bibRefCitation author="Duke, JA" journalOrPublisher="Lipid / Fett" pageId="172" pageNumber="173" refId="B34" refString="Duke, JA, Ayensu, ES, 1985. Medicinal Plants of China. 2 Vols. Reference Publications, Inc., Algonac." title="Medicinal Plants of China. 2 Vols. Reference Publications, Inc., Algonac." year="1985">Duke and Ayensu 1985</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
